OL,7,FHe also spoke to a male who got out of
OL,8,Fthe driver's side of the blazing car
OL,9,Fon the hard shoulder, the court heard.
OL,11,FMr Hudson told jurors: "I asked him
OL,12,Fwhere he was going and he was making
OL,13,Fsome motions away from me to my right
OL,14,Fand he just said 'up there' over the
OL,15,Fbarrier."
OL,17,FOn the conditions that night, he said:
OL,18,F"It was cold. It was a typical January
OL,19,Fat six o'clock at night as you would
OL,20,Fexpect, a winter's evening."
